## IMPORTANT INFORMATION FOR TENANT

### Time Limit for Court Proceedings

After the date specified above, court proceedings for possession may be begun at once but not later than 12 months from the date specified in this notice. After this time, the notice will lapse and a new notice must be served before proceedings can begin.

### Validity of Notice

This notice is invalid if:

- It does not specify the correct notice period for the ground(s) cited
- The ground(s) cited do not apply to your tenancy
- It does not give proper particulars of the ground(s)
- It does not comply with the requirements of the Housing Act 1988

If you believe this notice is invalid, seek legal advice immediately.

